Ti. Coruncanius, the first Plebeian who was elected Pontifex Maximus, is said by Cicero (Pro Plancio, c. 8) to have come from Tusculum. But the emperor Claudius in a speech reported by Tacitus (Anu. xi. 24) says that he was of Camerium, re·- marking at the same time that the Porcii were of Tusculum. Halm prefers this tes- timony to Cicero’s, of whom he remarks that he is not seldom inexact and careless in historical matters.
